#### **SECCIÓN 8.2: CI/CD PIPELINES EN KUBERNETES (GITHUB ACTIONS, GITLAB CI, JENKINS X)**

El pipeline CI/CD típico para GitOps:

1. **Push de código** a repositorio de aplicación.
2. **CI ejecuta:**
   - Tests unitarios y de integración.
   - Build de imagen Docker.
   - Escaneo de vulnerabilidades (Trivy, Snyk).
   - Firma de imagen (Cosign).
   - Push de imagen a registry (ECR, GCR, Docker Hub).
3. **Actualización automática** del repositorio de configuración (manifiestos) con la nueva etiqueta de imagen (Pull Request automático).
4. **ArgoCD/Flux** detecta el cambio en Git y sincroniza el clúster.
5. **Monitoreo** de rollout (Prometheus, Kiali) para detectar problemas.

**Ejemplo con GitHub Actions y ArgoCD Image Updater:**

```yaml
# .github/workflows/ci.yaml
name: CI/CD Pipeline

on:
  push:
    branches: [ main ]

env:
  REGISTRY: ghcr.io
  IMAGE_NAME: ${{ github.repository }}

jobs:
  build-and-push:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    permissions:
      contents: read
      packages: write
      id-token: write

    steps:
    - name: Checkout code
      uses: actions/checkout@v4

    - name: Set up Docker Buildx
      uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@v3

    - name: Log in to Container Registry
      uses: docker/login-action@v3
      with:
        registry: ${{ env.REGISTRY }}
        username: ${{ github.actor }}
        password: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}

    - name: Build and push Docker image
      uses: docker/build-push-action@v5
      with:
        context: .
        push: true
        tags: ${{ env.REGISTRY }}/${{ env.IMAGE_NAME }}:${{ github.sha }}
        cache-from: type=gha
        cache-to: type=gha,mode=max

    - name: Scan image for vulnerabilities (Trivy)
      uses: aquasecurity/trivy-action@master
      with:
        image-ref: ${{ env.REGISTRY }}/${{ env.IMAGE_NAME }}:${{ github.sha }}
        format: 'sarif'
        output: 'trivy-results.sarif'
        severity: 'CRITICAL,HIGH'

    - name: Upload Trivy results to GitHub Security tab
      uses: github/codeql-action/upload-sarif@v3
      with:
        sarif_file: 'trivy-results.sarif'

    - name: Sign image with Cosign
      run: |
        cosign sign -y ${{ env.REGISTRY }}/${{ env.IMAGE_NAME }}:${{ github.sha }} \
          --identity-token ${{ steps.id-token.outputs.token }}
      env:
        COSIGN_EXPERIMENTAL: true

    - name: Update Kubernetes manifests (PR automático)
      uses: peter-evans/create-pull-request@v5
      with:
        token: ${{ secrets.GITOPS_PAT }}
        repository: company/k8s-config
        branch: update-image-${{ github.sha }}
        title: "chore: update app image to ${{ github.sha }}"
        body: |
          Updated image to `${{ env.REGISTRY }}/${{ env.IMAGE_NAME }}:${{ github.sha }}`
          - Built from commit ${{ github.sha }}
          - Vulnerability scan: no CRITICAL or HIGH findings
          - Image signed with Cosign
        path: apps/myapp/overlays/production/kustomization.yaml
        commit-message: "Update image tag to ${{ github.sha }}"
```

